  "prompt": "How healthy is whole wheat?",
  "response": "Whole wheat is generally considered very healthy. Here are some key benefits:\n\n1. Nutritional profile\n- High in fiber\n- Contains essential vitamins (B vitamins)\n- Rich in minerals like iron, zinc, and magnesium\n- Provides complex carbohydrates\n\n2. Health benefits\n- Supports digestive health\n- Helps regulate blood sugar\n- May lower risk of heart disease\n- Can aid in weight management\n- Potentially reduces risk of type 2 diabetes\n\n3. Compared to refined wheat\n- Retains more nutrients\n- Contains all parts of the grain (bran, germ, endosperm)\n- Higher in fiber and protein\n- Lower glycemic index\n\n4. Potential considerations\n- Some people have gluten sensitivities\n- Can cause digestive issues for some individuals\n- Quality and processing can impact nutritional value\n\n5. Recommended consumption\n- Dietary guidelines suggest making at least half of grain intake whole grains\n- Aim for 3-5 servings per day\n\nOverall, whole wheat is a nutritious food that can be part of a healthy diet for most people.",
